snt.opts_order: ["1;You like him.;You do not like him.","2;Hug him for a long moment.;Shake his hand instead.","3;“Yup. It’s been a while. I’m still getting settled.”;“Yup. We should catch up! How about dinner soon?”","4;Turn around - you’re curious to see who he’s talking about.;Try to follow him, but it’s too late.","5;Get Chris’ point. The girl seems like a jerk.;Can’t help it. You like her immediately.","6;“I can’t - gotta go. Maybe tomorrow.”;You really don’t want to be late but reluctantly agree to grab coffee.","7;Nod and wait for him to invite you to his table. ;Point to an empty seat. “Sit here, save me the table.”","8;“So, how is everything? Catch me up!\";Try to avoid conversation by looking at your phone.","9;Space out and try to sort out your plans for the afternoon.;Ask for his other favorite spots around town - you need some recommendations.","10;You still have most of your coffee left but you order the new one instead.;“Thanks - but I’m still working on this one.” (You like your current coffee) ","11;You do not like her.;You like her.","12;“You owe me now.”;“It’s just because she knows my cousin.”","13;“Oh yeah. Move your bag to the trunk.”;“Oh – sure… I’ll move your bag to the trunk.” (Unfasten seatbelt and move bag to the trunk)","14;Immediately move over to the middle seat.;Wait for Chris to take the middle seat.","15;“Hello, nice meeting you.”;“Hi, nice to meet you.”","16;“She knew me when we were younger.”;“She knows my cousin.”","17;Change the subject. (How can he talk like that?);Nod while giving him a reassuring look. (You feel bad for him)","18;“Actually, I was going to sit there.” (Take the seat);“I’m good wherever. Maya, where do you think I should sit?”","19;“Mrs. Newcomb, I heard you have some issues in the office. How is that going…?”; “So, Nancy, how is Keith? What is he up to these days?”","20;Go to the website on your phone.;“Give them a call and schedule a meeting, please.”","21;“Thanks - but I already have so many references. I’ll definitely reach out if I need more.”;(Slightly uncomfortably) \"Ok… great.\"","22; “Ok, wait for me there, Mrs. Newcomb – I will meet you in a bit.”;You don’t feel like it but you were about to go check out that room anyway.","23;“Yes – she told me some things… But I’d rather keep it between her and I.”;“Yes – she told me some funny stories from back in the day, and told me to tell you she misses you, Nancy.”","24;“It’s ok - I’m fine standing.” ;There is a lot of clutter. You move it and sit like she told you.","25;“Whenever - it’s up to you.”;“We can leave in 30 minutes.”","26;Wait to see if Maya offers you a ride home.;“Let’s go, Maya. You’re driving me home.”","27;You don’t want to get between them, so you change the subject.;“He said a few things…” (Tell her everything Chris told you).","28;Sit across the table and change the topic.;(take a seat next to Maya) “I’d love to hear your idea!”","29;Sit where he directed you.;“I’m good here. Grab a chair and join us.”","30;Smile politely and wait to introduce yourself.;Stand aside while they talk and check your text messages.","31;“Let’s just schedule now. How’s Monday, 9 a.m.?”;“I’ll wait to hear from you, sir.”","32;“No, I’ll wait.”;“I’ll take a coffee, made fresh. I appreciate it.”","33;(Slightly bothered) “Fine,  I’ll wait.”;(On your way out) \"Tell Hayworth I’m free Wednesday morning.” ","34;(Check your email on your phone) “Is it always that hectic in here?”;“Looks like you’re the real person running this place - everybody really relies on you!” ","35;“I think that’s pretty common, actually.”;“Wow, they must really value you to have kept you that long!”","36;“Now I understand why you call this place Green-ville.”;“Yes, it’s much nicer than yesterday.”","37;You’re annoyed at having to walk over there, but you do.;Wave back at her to come join you.","38;“This is part of chapter 3.\";“Take this - make sure it’s in the proposal.\"","39;(Are bored) “Is anyone else joining for dinner?” Try to make small talk.;Want to get to know Kayce. “So, do you have family here, Kayce?”","40;“I’ll try but I have a lot going on right now.”;“Absolutely, we have a lot to talk about.”","41;(Glad he asked) Tell him everything you’ve been through in the last few weeks.;“I’m still trying to make it work.”","42;Ask about his favorite things about Hayworth Industries.;Study the menu to decide what you want to eat, without replying.","43;(Talking to the waiter) “I’ll actually have that last special instead.” ;It’s not what you wanted, but it’s already ordered.","44;“You seem to get along with everyone in the community.” ;(You’re bored with the conversation) \"You work with everyone, huh?\"","45;(You nervously change the subject) “The food is great here.”; (Laughing) “Oh yes, especially Mrs. Newcomb...”","46;“I’m interested, but I have other offers.”;“I really need this job. It’s been really tough.”","47;Go for a handshake instead.;Smile and hug her back.","48;“Damn, I’m tired. I just wanna finish my food and go home.”;“How’s your business idea coming? Any more meetings with Mrs. Newcomb?”","49;Turn away to avoid her, but she spots you and comes over to say hi.;(Waving at her to come over) “Kayce, this is Maya. You are welcome to join us.”","50;“The waiter will come by in a minute.”;“Do you know Kayce? Hayworth’s assistant?” (Tell Maya about Kayce)","51;(Laughing) “Don’t be ridiculous!”;(Moving away) “Don’t be ridiculous.\"","52;This is not in your job description, but you’ll do it anyway.;“I’m sorry, but I can’t make it – I already have another meeting scheduled. Maybe Kayce can do it?”","53;Reluctantly stay overtime.;Work hard, but stick to the hiring contract and don’t stay overtime.","54;“Yeah, I knew I would nail it.” ;“I would never get it without someone pulling some strings.”","55;“Yes – I am excited to work on these projects with you!”;“We’ll see. First I have a lot to work on.”","56;“Start with these. My assistant will give you the rest tomorrow.”;“Oh - okay. I suppose I’ll get to work on those now, then.”","57;(Don’t want to get involved) “I’ll give you privacy. I think we’re done, anyway.”;(Feel concerned) “Everything alright, Nancy? What is it?”","58;(Reach out to hold her shoulder) “Oh no, I’m so sorry.”;“Ok - we’ll continue later.” ","59;Grab one of the ads and put in your pocket.;“Send me the terms. I’ll have my assistant take a look.” ","60;Slightly annoyed, you take a look at the document.;“Can we talk about that later? Now I need you to help me get some documents signed.”","61;“Let me know when you have some more information.”;“Get me the contract and floor plan and tell them you need ’til tomorrow.”","62;You hate when she bosses you around, but drop off the dry cleaning anyway.;“I can’t, maybe just leave it here and do it tomorrow?”","63;“Thanks for the offer, Kayce, but I am actually going to rent from Nancy.”;“Let’s live together. I think we would be great housemates.”"]
